public int stringSumScores(String s){
    int score = 0;
    int prefix_length = 0;

    for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(s.length() - 1)) {
            prefix_length++;
        } else {
            prefix_length = 0;
        }
        score += prefix_length;
    }
    return score;
}

```


    The algorithm starts iterating from the end of the string `s` to the beginning. For each character, it checks if the character is equal to the last character of the string. If the character is equal, it increases the `prefix_length` counter, otherwise, it resets the `prefix_length` to 0. We update the `score` by adding the `prefix_length` after each iteration.

As we are prepending the new characters to the front of the string, iterating in reverse order will generate the desired strings (s_i) in the correct order.
